Parliament, Wednesday, 26 May 2021 – The Portfolio Committee on Higher Education, Science and Technology and the Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sport, Arts and Culture will tomorrow be briefed by the Department of Higher Education and Training on the analysis of lessons learnt in respect of the multimodal teaching and learning mechanisms during the lockdown period in the Post School Education and Training system. The committees will also be briefed by the Department of Education and Training on registration for the 2021 academic year for universities and the TVET colleges. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 26 May 2021 Time: 09:00-13:00 Virtual Meeting Platform. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Mava Lukani (Mr)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
